contents.name: Unit of Account
contents.description: The right to inflow or the group of rights, the obligation to outflow or the group of obligations, or the group of rights and obligations, to which recognition criteria and measurement concepts are applied.

contents.name: Reciprocity Relator
contents.description:
An [enabling or entitling] right that has the potential to produce economic benefits,    
including the right to assume a new economic (claim).

contents.name: Equity Claim
contents.description: The residual interest in the assets of the entity after deducting all its liabilities.

contents.name: Outflow
contents.description:
Outflows include Services Provided by Inflow events and/or Crediting events causing termination of Assets, creation of Liabilities for the creation of Resources Transferred to the other party, termination of (Claims) Transferred from the other party, resulting in Equity Decrease.   
  
[1] In IFRS parlance: the derecognition of an asset, or a decrease in the carrying amount of an asset [1:5.4]

contents.name: Inflow
contents.description: Inflows include termination of the Resources Transferred from the other party, creation of the (Claims) Transferred to the other party, and Debiting events causing creation of Assets, termination of Liabilities and/or Services Provided event,resulting in Equity Increase.

contents.name: Asset
contents.description:
A present economic resource controlled by the entity as a result of past events. 


An entity controls an economic resource if it has the present ability to direct the use of the economic resource and obtain the economic benefits that may flow from it,  
either directly or through an agent acting on behalf of the controlling entity.   
Control includes the present ability to prevent other parties from directing the use of the economic resource and from obtaining the economic benefits that may flow from it.   
An agent may facilitate the obtaining of economic benefits or the prevention of others from obtaining such benefits, but the principal retains ultimate control.   
It follows that, if one party controls an economic resource, no other party controls that resource.

contents.name: Revenue
contents.description: Income arising in the course of an entity’s ordinary activities when transferring goods or services to customers in exchange for consideration.

contents.name: Claim to
contents.description: An entitling right that corresponds to an obligation of another party

contents.name: Liability
contents.description:
A present obligation of the entity to transfer an economic resource   
or to provide services or to assume a new economic (claim)   
as a result of past events.

contents.name: Distribution
contents.description: Decreases in equity of an entity resulting from transferring assets, rendering services, or incurring liabilities by the entity to owners. Distributions to owners decrease ownership interest (or equity) in an entity.

contents.name: Investment
contents.description: Increases in equity of an entity resulting from transfers to the entity from other entities of something valuable to obtain or increase interests (or equity) in the entity.

contents.name: Expense
contents.description:
Decreases in assets, or increases in liabilities   
or services received that are immediately consumed, required to produce outflow,   
that result in decreases in equity, other than those relating to distributions to holders of equity claims.

contents.name: Income
contents.description:
Increases in assets, or decreases in liabilities,   
or services received that are immediately consumed, produced from the inflow   
that result in increases in equity, other than those relating to contributions from holders of equity claims.

contents.name: Loss
contents.description: Decreases in equity from transactions and other events and circumstances affecting an entity except those that result from expenses or distributions to owners.

contents.name: Gain
contents.description: Increases in equity from transactions and other events and circumstances affecting an entity except those that result from revenues or investments by owners.

contents.name: Exchange Engagement
contents.description: An entity has the present ability to direct the use of an economic resource if it has the right to deploy that economic resource in its activities, or to allow another party, such as an agent, to deploy the economic resource in that other party’s activities.

contents.name: Outflow Engagement
contents.description: A present obligation of an agent to transfer to a third party an economic resource controlled by the principal.

contents.name: 1. Financial Performance
contents.description: 1. Changes in economic resources and claims reflecting financial performance.

contents.name: 1.1. Ordinary Activity
contents.description: 1.1 Changes from ordinary activities

contents.name: 1.2. Other Event
contents.description: 1.2 Changes from not ordinary activities

contents.name: 2.2. Other Change
contents.description: Exchanges of assets or liabilities that do not result in increases or decreases in equity.

contents.name: Operating Expense
contents.description: Outflows or other using up of assets of an entity or incurrences of its liabilities from delivering or producing goods, rendering services, or carrying out other activities.

contents.name: Claim from
contents.description:
Liability or Equity (Claim).   
An obligation that has the potential to sacrifice economic benefits,  
including the obligation to assume a new economic (claim).

contents.name: Exchange Contract
contents.description: A combined right and obligation to exchange economic resources. The right and obligation are interdependent and cannot be separated. Hence, the combined right and obligation constitute a single asset or liability.

contents.name: Economic Claim Type
contents.description:
Liability or Equity (Claim).   
An obligation that has the potential to sacrifice economic benefits,  
including the obligation to assume a new economic (claim).

contents.name: Economic Benefit
contents.description: Inflow of economic resources or outflow of economic (claims)

A present obligation of the entity to transfer an economic resource   
or to provide services or to assume a new economic (claim)
